item.description:
@Aesyr wrote:

I hate to break it to you, but if you can’t figure out how to portforward and someone has to do it for you, you should not be hosting a server.

Now, I didn’t say you shouldn’t OWN a server, but you definitely should not host one. There will be more problems in the future that you will have no idea how to fix if you try to do it yourself without knowledge on how your own internet works.

item.title: Error....-.-'
item.dc:creator: @yodead yodead
item.description:
@yodead wrote:

(server listening on port : insanepvp.no-ip.biz : 43594)

When you run your server, you can just keep it on 0.0.0.0:43594. But I don’t think thats the problem. What kind of client are you using?

EDIT: Runelocus says your server is offline, and I just tried connecting to it using a PI client. Make sure you have your no-ip running. Because it’s something wrong with the connection, not the client.
